**To find the sum of the 8 neighbors of 2026 in the given spiral grid (where 1 is at the center, starting rightward then spiraling counterclockwise), first determine its layer and position.**

The spiral is structured in **layers** (squares) around the center 1 at (0,0), with layer \( l \) (starting at \( l=0 \) for 1) spanning numbers from \( (2l-1)^2 + 1 \) to \( (2l+1)^2 \). Layer sizes increase: layer 1 (3×3, numbers 2–9), layer 2 (5×5, 10–25), etc.[2]

For 2026, solve for layer \( l \): \( (2l+1)^2 \geq 2026 \). The side length \( 2l+1 = \lceil \sqrt{2026} \rceil = 45 \) (since \( 44^2 = 1936 \), \( 45^2 = 2025 \), \( 46^2 = 2116 \)), so \( l = 22 \) (side 45, numbers up to 2025). Thus, 2026 starts layer 23 at position (23, -22), right of 2025 at (22, -22).[2]

The 8 neighbors of (23, -22) are: (22,-23), (22,-22), (22,-21), (23,-23), **(23,-21)**, (24,-23), (24,-22), (24,-21).

Using the number-at-position formula (adjusted for this spiral's origin and counterclockwise direction from [2]):

| Position (y,x) | Formula Case | Value |
|----------------|--------------|-------|
| (22,-23)      | \( x < -y \) (\( y \) odd) | \( 2025 + (23 - (-23)) = 2025 + 46 = 2071 \) |
| (22,-22)      | Inner square edge | 2025 |
| (22,-21)      | \( \|x\| < y \) (\( y \) even) | \( 1937 + 44 - 21 = 1960 \) |
| (23,-23)      | \( x < -y \) (\( y \) odd) | \( 2116 - (23 - (-23)) = 2116 - 46 = 2070 \) |
| (23,-21)      | Bottom side | \( 2025 + 2 = 2027 \) |
| (24,-23)      | \( x < -y \) (\( y \) even) | \( 2116 - (24 - (-23)) = 2116 - 47 = 2069 \) |
| (24,-22)      | Left side | \( 2116 - 24 = 2092 \) |
| (24,-21)      | \( \|x\| < y \) (\( y \) even) | \( 2025 + 47 + 21 = 2093 \) | [2]

**Sum: 2071 + 2025 + 1960 + 2070 + 2027 + 2069 + 2092 + 2093 = 16{,}507**.[2]

